    "author_association": "COLLABORATOR",
    "body": "As discussed on the call I propose to implement as database backed state (see #330). This shouldn't clash with most of the chain sync work. Currently you can use the optimized state that stores stuff in memory and will probably run into current limitations of spec before you run out of memory.\r\n\r\nIf you decide to store blocks (which are not part of the state) in a database we should probably coordinate on which one (I think the main candidates are LevelDB and LMDB).",
